Volunteer — Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival Home Food Rides Entertainment Exhibitors Sponsors T-Shirts Contact Back Volunteer Directions Contact Us Home Food Rides Entertainment Exhibitors Sponsors T-Shirts Contact Volunteer Directions Contact Us Volunteer, Sponsor or Donate The Frog Leg Festival has come a long way since the first 400 dinners sold in 1990.  The success of this annual event is due to a very dedicated and hard working group of volunteers who come out every year to help serve up these frog leg dinners to thousands of people.  Over the years, this group of people has helped raise over $1,000,000 that has been contributed back to the City Of Fellsmere for the recreational needs of the children and to the dozens of volunteer groups and organizations who come out to help put on the festival. We are always looking for volunteers to help with the organization and execution of the Frog Leg Festival.  If you are interested in volunteering your time and talents please fill out the form below and our Volunteer Coordinator will contact you. Volunteer opportunities include, but are not limited to: Ticket Sales, Beverage Sales, Food Preparation and Kitchen Duties, Volunteer Coordination, Site Management and Entertainment Support. Let us know how you'd like to get in on the gig that's been supporting Fellsmere's youth for 33 years! Name * First Name Last Name Email Address * Phone # Be a big frog in a small pond! Result View All Result Home Community News in Sebastian, Florida 34th Annual Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival: Rides, Food, Live Music by Tina Hodges Jan 8, 2025 / 1:45 PM A A A A Reset Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share via Email Celebrate a January tradition at the 34th Annual Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival , held January 16th–19th at 22 South Orange St., Fellsmere, Florida. Enjoy carnival rides, live music, and delicious food, including frog legs, gator tails, and more. With exhibitors and other attractions, there’s something for everyone. Similar to last year , proceeds benefit the recreational needs of Fellsmere’s youth and senior league ball fields. Join the fun and discover why this festival is a beloved annual event. Festival Schedule Thursday & Friday 4:00 pm – 11:00 pm Saturday 10:00 am – 11:00 pm Sunday 11:00 am – 6:00 pm All-You-Can-Ride Days Purchase an armband and ride as many rides as you want – for the entire night! Thursday & Sunday: Get your Armband for just $20 Friday & Saturday: Get your Armband for $25 Carnival Rides (Tickets) 1 Ticket: $1.25 18 Tickets: $20 Purchase an armband for unlimited rides: Thursday night, January 16 & Sunday, January 19 for $20 Purchase an armband for unlimited rides: Friday night, January 19 & Saturday, January 20 for $25 Food Schedule Thursday & Friday: 4:00 pm to 8:00 pm Saturday: 11:00 am to 8:00 pm Sunday: 11:00 am to 4:00 pm Frog  Menu Frog Pop – $5: The perfect way to sample a frog! One frog leg on a stick. No sides included. Frog Leg Dinner – $18: A generous portion of frog legs served with grits, coleslaw, and hushpuppies Frog Pounder – $17: A full pound of delicious frog legs. No sides included. Gator Menu Gator Pop – $5: The perfect way to sample alligator, receive a couple of chunks of gator tail on a stick. No sides included. Gator Tail Dinner – $18: A generous portion of gator tail served with grits, coleslaw, and hushpuppies. Gator Pounder – $17: A pound of delicious gator tail. No sides included. Combos & Sides Menu Frog Legs & Gator Tail Combo – $20: A generous portion of gator tail and frog legs served with grits, coleslaw, and hushpuppies. Extra side orders – $3: Hushpuppies, coleslaw, or grits. Drive-Thru To accommodate all of its loyal fans, they are offering a drive-thru pick-up option located at 21 S Cypress Street. Please enter the drive-thru line off South Cypress Street. Follow the Take-Out signs to place your order, pay, and pick up your meals. You get frog legs for dinner without getting out of your car. Entertainment Schedule Thursday 4:00pm – 6:00 pm | Johnny Debt 7:00 pm – 9:00 pm | Dragon’s Breath Friday 4:00 pm – 6:00 pm | James Holler 6:30 pm – 9:00 pm | Three O’Clock Storm Saturday 12:00 pm – 2:00 pm | Becks Brothers 2:00 pm – 5:00 pm | Doolin Dalton 3:00 pm – 4:00 pm | Fellsmere Elementary Music Club Performance 5:30 pm – 8:30 pm | Chemistry 9:00 pm – 11:00 pm | Hi Mileage Sunday 11:00 am – 1:00 pm | Penny Creek Band 2:00 pm – 4:00 pm | Nex Level Rides, Food & Games Roller coasters and amusements for all ages will range from 3 to 4 tickets each or $3.75 – $5.00. Additional Food & Drink Options Corn dogs, Funnel cakes, Cheesesteaks, Pizza, Turkey legs, Gyros, Hot dogs, Burgers, Kabobs, and fried Snickers will range between 4 and 10 tickets per item. Cash-Only. Arnold Amusements will provide all carnival rides, food, and games. For more information about the Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival, visit their website or call 772-571-3022 or email them . The Latest News Hop on over to the Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival for a frogtastic good time! Alastair Mac Jan 14 2 min read The Fellsmere Frog Festival is celebrating it's 34th anniversary, with all proceeds going to the Fellsmere community in Indian River County. Join the 34th Annual Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival for a true taste of Florida! Savor delicious frog leg and gator tail dinners, browse hundreds of booths with unique gifts, enjoy live local music, and thrill at the fun rides. Discover why this January festival has become a cherished tradition year after year, with this year's Fellsmere Frog Leg Festival taking place from January 16 - 19, 2025. This Guinness Book of World Record holder event is famous of course for the mouth-watering frog leg and gator tail dinners! Options include a Frog Pop or a Gator Pop, a frog leg, or a gator tail on a stick, or you can enjoy a Frog Leg, or Gator Tail Dinner, featuring a generous portion of frog legs, or gator tail, served with grits, coleslaw, and hushpuppies! While you chow down on your food, the festival features live entertainment, including performances from Penny Creek Band, Becks Brithers, Johhny Debt and more! The world's largest frogs leg festival also features a huge carnival with all the fun of the fair for all the family. Best of all this family-friendly festival offers Free Parking. Free Admission, and a frogtastic amount of fun! I’m Stephanie Nace, the proud founder of Frogleg Studio, which I started way back in 2001. I’ve always been a bit “extra” when it comes to details, originality, and pouring my heart into my work. With over two decades as a design educator and even longer as a creative professional, I absolutely love teaming up with students and clients to bring fresh, exciting ideas to life. Then, in 2022, Paul joined both my life and the studio—and let me tell you, he’s “extra,” too! With his background in electrical engineering, he’s a stickler for precision, craftsmanship, and making sure everything in the studio runs like clockwork. Together, we’ve found the perfect mix of craftsmanship, typography, and illustration, which shines through in our letterpress work. Everything we design is one-of-a-kind and created just for you. Once it leaves our studio, it’s never repeated. It’s all about capturing your personality, quirks, and style. At Frogleg Studio, we offer custom graphic design, letterpress, foil printing, risograph printing, die cuts, and debossing. Got an idea? We’ll bring it to life! We’re all about creating one-of-a-kind designs that fit you —and your budget (because stunning shouldn’t mean scary expensive). Wedding investments start around $6K, but the sky’s the limit depending on how fancy you want to get. No cookie-cutter designs here—every piece is custom-made just for you, never to be repeated. And don’t worry, you have our full, undivided attention—no distractions (except maybe for tea breaks). Plus, we print everything in-house on one of our four presses, which helps keep costs reasonable—because who doesn’t love a little luxury without the sticker shock? Let’s make something unforgettable! Here's how the magic happens! Once we get your inquiry form, we’ll set up a Blue Skies Meeting. This is where you share all the juicy details about your big day—your dreams, ideas, and visions for the ceremony and reception. We want to hear all about your style, your love story, the little moments that make your relationship unique. How did you meet? What was your first date like? The more details, the better! This info helps us create a wedding suite that’s as one-of-a-kind as you are. After our meeting and the $500 proposal fee, I’ll provide a custom quote and mood board, giving you a preview of your wedding suite’s vibe. This also ensures your date is officially locked in on our creative calendar Once you fall head over heels for your custom mood board, sign the contract and pay the 50% retainer—then the fun really begins! We’ll dive into creating your personalized color palette, custom illustrations, letterpress designs, and all the day-of materials. You’ll be involved every step of the way, from the sketches to the final proofs, ensuring everything feels just right. Finally, it’s time to bring your vision to life! A team of talented artisans, from papermakers to vintage stamp curators to ink mixers, will work their magic, ensuring your design comes together flawlessly. The end result? A stunning wedding suite that tells your story in the most beautiful way possible. Let’s Talk We are looking forward to collabrating.
